==English==
===Alternative spellings===
* '''[[Commonise]]'''

===Verb===
{{en-infl-irreg|Commonize|Commonizes|Commonizing|Commonized|Commonized}}

# To make [[similar]] two or more [[differences]] by way of [[intentional]] [[process]].
#:''He attempted to '''commonize''' the various standards by ensuring a similar format and implementation.''
# To [[deprecate]] the [[importance]] of, or make [[ordinary]], a [[noun]] or nouns.
#:''She gave each participant a trophy, regardless of win or loss, to '''commonize''' the award for winning.''

===Usage notes===
"'''Commonize'''" has a widespread use in all of its various word forms, especially in business and manufacturing:
